apacheModVersion.name: apacheModVersion
apacheModVersion.description: Description and version number of this module for licensing.

apacheModMode.name: apacheModMode
apacheModMode.description: This object indicates if the Apache Module is in full-mode or restricted-mode. Restricted-mode is entered, when SystemEDGE 4.0 and higher, fails to find a valid license. Once a valid license has been allocated and set, the module will then transition to fullMode(1)

apacheConfigTable.name: apacheConfigTable
apacheConfigTable.description: This table describes the configuration settings for each Apache installation.

apacheConfigEntry.name: apacheConfigEntry
apacheConfigEntry.description: An entry in the Apache Configuration table.

apacheConfigPort.name: apacheConfigPort
apacheConfigPort.description: The TCP port currently used by this Apache configuration. This value serves as the index for this table.

apacheConfigVersion.name: apacheConfigVersion
apacheConfigVersion.description: Apache Web Server version number and description.

apacheConfigPID.name: apacheConfigPID
apacheConfigPID.description: The process ID (PID) of the master Apache process. If the server is not running, 0 is returned.

apacheConfigUser.name: apacheConfigUser
apacheConfigUser.description: The user currently running the server processes.

apacheConfigGroup.name: apacheConfigGroup
apacheConfigGroup.description: The group currently running the server processes.

apacheConfigHostname.name: apacheConfigHostname
apacheConfigHostname.description: The hostname used by this Apache configuration.

apacheConfigStartProcs.name: apacheConfigStartProcs
apacheConfigStartProcs.description: The number of server processes started by Apache at startup.

apacheConfigMinIdleProcs.name: apacheConfigMinIdleProcs
apacheConfigMinIdleProcs.description: The minimum number of idle server processes maintained by Apache.

apacheConfigMaxIdleProcs.name: apacheConfigMaxIdleProcs
apacheConfigMaxIdleProcs.description: The maximum number of idle server processes maintained by Apache.

apacheConfigMaxProcs.name: apacheConfigMaxProcs
apacheConfigMaxProcs.description: The maximum total number of server processes allowed by Apache.

apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerChild.name: apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerChild
apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerChild.description: The number of requests handled by a server process before it is recycled by Apache.

apacheConfigRequestsKeepAlive.name: apacheConfigRequestsKeepAlive
apacheConfigRequestsKeepAlive.description: Is keep-alive enabled for persistent connections? disabled(0) or enabled(1)

apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerConn.name: apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerConn
apacheConfigRequestsMaxPerConn.description: The number of requests handled in a single connection if keep-alive is on.

apacheConfigThreadsPerChild.name: apacheConfigThreadsPerChild
apacheConfigThreadsPerChild.description: The maximum number of threads per child process.

apacheConfigConnectionTimeout.name: apacheConfigConnectionTimeout
apacheConfigConnectionTimeout.description: The timeout value for closing inactive connections.

apacheConfigKeepAliveTimeout.name: apacheConfigKeepAliveTimeout
apacheConfigKeepAliveTimeout.description: The keep-alive timeout value for open connections.

apacheConfigServerRoot.name: apacheConfigServerRoot
apacheConfigServerRoot.description: The root directory for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigConfigFile.name: apacheConfigConfigFile
apacheConfigConfigFile.description: The current configuration file for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigPIDFile.name: apacheConfigPIDFile
apacheConfigPIDFile.description: The current PID file for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigScoreboardFile.name: apacheConfigScoreboardFile
apacheConfigScoreboardFile.description: The current scoreboard file for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigDocumentRoot.name: apacheConfigDocumentRoot
apacheConfigDocumentRoot.description: The current document root directory for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigAccessLogFile.name: apacheConfigAccessLogFile
apacheConfigAccessLogFile.description: The current access or transaction log file for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigErrorLogFile.name: apacheConfigErrorLogFile
apacheConfigErrorLogFile.description: The current error log file for this Apache installation.

apacheConfigScriptLogFile.name: apacheConfigScriptLogFile
apacheConfigScriptLogFile.description: The current script log file for this Apache installation.

apacheFootprintTable.name: apacheFootprintTable
apacheFootprintTable.description: This table reports the performance footprint for each Apache service.

apacheFootprintEntry.name: apacheFootprintEntry
apacheFootprintEntry.description: An entry in the Apache Performance Footprint table.

apacheFootprintPort.name: apacheFootprintPort
apacheFootprintPort.description: The TCP port currently used by this Apache configuration. This value serves as the index for this table.

apacheFootprintCPUTime.name: apacheFootprintCPUTime
apacheFootprintCPUTime.description: CPU time, in seconds, accumulated by Apache which includes all Apache processes.

apacheFootprintPercentCPU.name: apacheFootprintPercentCPU
apacheFootprintPercentCPU.description: The percentage of CPU utilization, by Apache, over the last sample interval. Since fractions are not supported by SNMP, the value reported is the percentage multiplied by 100. It is the sum of the CPU utilization of all the Apache processes. Its gives a good indication of the CPU resource consumption by the entire Apache server.

apacheFootprintTotalMEMSize.name: apacheFootprintTotalMEMSize
apacheFootprintTotalMEMSize.description: The combined size of Apache's text, data, and stack segments in KBytes. It is the summation of the process sizes for all Apache server processes.

apacheFootprintTotalRSS.name: apacheFootprintTotalRSS
apacheFootprintTotalRSS.description: The real memory (resident set) size of Apache in KBytes. It is the summation of the process RSS for all Apache server processes.

apacheFootprintPercentMEM.name: apacheFootprintPercentMEM
apacheFootprintPercentMEM.description: The percentage (0-100) of real memory used by Apache which includes all Apache server processes.

apacheFootprintNumThreads.name: apacheFootprintNumThreads
apacheFootprintNumThreads.description: The number of threads executing within all Apache processes. Note, on some systems, the operating system may be un-aware of user-level threads executing within the process. This object reflects the number of threads executing within the process that the operating system is aware of.

apacheFootprintInBlks.name: apacheFootprintInBlks
apacheFootprintInBlks.description: The number of blocks of data input by the processes.

apacheFootprintOutBlks.name: apacheFootprintOutBlks
apacheFootprintOutBlks.description: The number of blocks of data output by the processes.

apacheFootprintMsgsSent.name: apacheFootprintMsgsSent
apacheFootprintMsgsSent.description: The number of messages sent by the processes.

apacheFootprintMsgsRecv.name: apacheFootprintMsgsRecv
apacheFootprintMsgsRecv.description: The number of messages received by the processes.

apacheFootprintSysCalls.name: apacheFootprintSysCalls
apacheFootprintSysCalls.description: The number of system calls invoked by the processes.

apacheFootprintMinorPgFlts.name: apacheFootprintMinorPgFlts
apacheFootprintMinorPgFlts.description: The number of minor page faults incurred by the processes. Minor faults do not require I/O to retrieve the page.

apacheFootprintMajorPgFlts.name: apacheFootprintMajorPgFlts
apacheFootprintMajorPgFlts.description: The number of major page faults incurred by the processes. Major faults require I/O to retrieve the page.

apacheFootprintNumSwaps.name: apacheFootprintNumSwaps
apacheFootprintNumSwaps.description: The number of times the processes have been swapped.

apacheFootprintVolCtx.name: apacheFootprintVolCtx
apacheFootprintVolCtx.description: The number of voluntary context switches incurred by the processes. Voluntary context switches occur when the processor 'voluntary' gives up the CPU (e.g. waiting on I/O.)

apacheFootprintInvolCtx.name: apacheFootprintInvolCtx
apacheFootprintInvolCtx.description: The number of involuntary context switches incurred by the processes. An involuntary context switch occurs when the process has executed for the duration of its time quantum and is switched out by the process scheduler.

apacheFootprintTotalLogSize.name: apacheFootprintTotalLogSize
apacheFootprintTotalLogSize.description: The size, in KBytes of the Apache service logs. This number is the sum of the access and error log file sizes.

apacheFootprintDocSize.name: apacheFootprintDocSize
apacheFootprintDocSize.description: The size, in KBytes of the Apache document root directory and all files beneath it.

apacheFootprintTotalDiskSize.name: apacheFootprintTotalDiskSize
apacheFootprintTotalDiskSize.description: The size, in KBytes, of all the Apache disk storage areas. It is a summation of log sizes, and service directories. Summing these storage components in one location presents an easy and convenient MIB object to poll and self-monitor.

apacheServerPerfTable.name: apacheServerPerfTable
apacheServerPerfTable.description: This table reports the performance of each Apache service.

apacheServerPerfEntry.name: apacheServerPerfEntry
apacheServerPerfEntry.description: An entry in the Apache Server Performance table.

apacheServerPerfPort.name: apacheServerPerfPort
apacheServerPerfPort.description: The TCP port currently used by this Apache configuration. This value serves as the index for this table.

apacheServerPerfUptime.name: apacheServerPerfUptime
apacheServerPerfUptime.description: Number of seconds the Apache server has been up.

apacheServerPerfTotalAccesses.name: apacheServerPerfTotalAccesses
apacheServerPerfTotalAccesses.description: Number of accesses (hits) to this server since it was last started.

apacheServerPerfTotalTraffic.name: apacheServerPerfTotalTraffic
apacheServerPerfTotalTraffic.description: Number of KBytes transferred by this server since it was last started.

apacheServerPerfCurrentUsers.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentUsers
apacheServerPerfCurrentUsers.description: Number of current active users (connections) maintained by the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentIdleProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentIdleProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentIdleProcs.description: Number of current idle processes available on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentStartupProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentStartupProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentStartupProcs.description: Number of processes currently in startup on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentReadProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentReadProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentReadProcs.description: Number of processes currently reading requests on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentReplyProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentReplyProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentReplyProcs.description: Number of processes currently replying to requests on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentKeepAliveProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentKeepAliveProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentKeepAliveProcs.description: Number of processes currently in keep-alive on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentDNSProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentDNSProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentDNSProcs.description: Number of processes currently doing a DNS lookup on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentLoggingProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentLoggingProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentLoggingProcs.description: Number of processes currently logging transactions on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentFinishingProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentFinishingProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentFinishingProcs.description: Number of processes currently finishing transactions on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentTotalProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentTotalProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentTotalProcs.description: Total number of Apache processes currently running on the Apache server.

apacheServerPerfCurrentBusyProcs.name: apacheServerPerfCurrentBusyProcs
apacheServerPerfCurrentBusyProcs.description: Total number of Apache processes currently busy. This is the sum of apacheServerPerfCurrentStartupProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentReadProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentReplyProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentKeepAliveProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentDNSProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentLoggingProcs, apacheServerPerfCurrentFinishingProcs
